<p>The llms.txt file fixes this. It is a plain-text Markdown file that sits in your root directory and tells large language models exactly which pages to read. Think of it as a curated table of contents for AI. Not a blocker like <a href="/blog/optimize-robots-txt/">robots.txt</a>. Not a discovery map like your <a href="/blog/create-xml-sitemap/">XML sitemap</a>. A curation layer.</p>
